sodes\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2017 || ''[[Teachers (2016 TV series)|Teachers]]'' || Ayo || Episode: \"Brokebitch Mountain\"\n|-\n| ''[[Little Big Shots]]'' || Himself || Episode: \"Memory Lane\"\n|-\n| ''[[I'm Dying Up Here]]'' || Adam\u2019s brother || Episode: \"The Unbelievable Power of Believing\"\n|-\n| 2018\u2013present || ''[[The Paynes]]'' || Kenny Payne || \n|-\n| 2019 || ''[[American Soul]]'' || [[Michael Jackson|Young Michael Jackson]] || Episode: \"68 BC\"\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{IMDb name}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:McCrary, JD}}\n[[Category:Male actors from Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:American child singers]]\n[[Category:2007 births]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2018}}\n{{Infobox actor\n| name =JD McCrary\n| image =\n| caption = \n| birth_name = Jaydon McCrary\n| birth_date = July 18, 2007 (age 12)\n| birth_place = [[Granada Hills, Los Angeles]], [[California]], United States\n| occupation = Singer, dancer, actor\n| years_active = 2014\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Jaydon McCrary'''<ref name=\"IMDb\">{{cite web |title=JD McCrary |url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm6556377/ |website=IMDb}}</ref> (born July 18, 2007) is an American singer, dancer and actor. He is currently starring in ''[[The Paynes]]'' as Kenny Payne on the [[Oprah Winfrey Network]]. He starred in 2019's ''[[The Lion King (2019 film)|The Lion King]]'' as the voice of young [[Simba]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=George|first1=Rachel|title=5 Things to Know About JD McCrary, Childish Gambino's Young Grammys Co-Star|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/grammys/8096915/childish-gambino-jd-mccrary-5-things-to-know|website=Billboard|date=January 29, 2018|accessdate=February 21, 2018}}</ref> He is signed to [[Hollywood Records]] and released his first extended play ''Shine'', in April 2019. He also appeared in the song \"Keep In Touch\" on ''[[Just Dance 2020]]''.\n\n==Career==\nMcCrary began his acting career in 2015 at age 8 on ''[[K.C. Undercover]]'', where he appeared on two episodes.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Canter|first1=Brian|title=First Look: \"KC Undercover\" Returns With \"Undercover Mother,\" \"Trust No One Episodes|url=http://headlineplanet.com/home/2016/11/02/first-look-kc-undercover-returns-undercover-mother-trust-no-one-episodes/|website=Headline Planet|date=November 2, 2016|accessdate=February 21, 2018}}</ref> In December 2016, he made a guest appearance on [[Donald Glover|Childish Gambino]]'s song \"[[Terrified (song)|Terrified]]\".<ref>{{cite web|last1=Starling|first1=Lankan|title=JD McCrary Is The Precocious 9 Year-Old Singing on Childish Gambino's \"Terrified\"|url=http://www.thefader.com/2016/12/06/jd-mccrary-featured-zombies-awaken-my-love|website=The Fader|date=December 6, 2016|accessdate=February 21, 2018}}</ref> He then had live performances on ''[[Little Big Shots]]'' singing [[The Jackson 5]]'s \"[[I Want You Back]]\",<ref>{{cite web|last1=Cheatle|first1=Juliet|title=JD McCrary: Who is child singing sensation from Little Big Shots?|url=https://www.monstersandcritics.com/smallscreen/jd-mccrary-who-is-child-singing-sensation-from-little-big-shots/|website=Monsters and Critics|date=May 14, 2017|accessdate=February 21, 2018}}</ref> ''[[The Ellen Show]]'' singing \"[[Who's Lovin' You]]\",<ref>{{cite web|last1=Reddy|first1=Subba|title=Kid Singer JD McCrary Wows with \u2018Who's Loving You\u2019 Performance The Ellen Show|url=http://whateverlife.com/kid-singer-jd-mccrary-wows-with-whos-loving-you-performance-the-ellen-show-on-whateverlife/|website=Whatever Life|date=January 15, 2018|accessdate=February 21, 2018}}</ref> and the [[60th Annual Grammy Awards]] to support Childish Gambino's \"Terrified\".<ref>{{cite web|last1=Nyren|first1=Eric|title=Donald Glover Sang With the Voice of \u2018The Lion King's\u2019 Young Simba at the Grammys|url=https://variety.com/2018/music/news/childish-gambino-grammys-performance-kid-1202679775/|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=January 28, 2018|accessdate=February 21, 2018}}</ref> In December 2017, he sang the national anthem before a [[Los Angeles Clippers]] game after a viral singing display a few weeks prior.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Keaney |first1=Quinn |title=The Actor Playing Young Simba in The Lion King Reboot Blew NBA Fans Away With His Voice |url=https://www.popsugar.com/entertainment/JD-McCrary-Singing-LA-Clippers-Game-Video-44352387 |website=Pop Sugar}}</ref> In 2017, he later appeared on ''[[I'm Dying Up Here]]'' and ''[[Teachers (2016 TV series)|Teachers]]'' as minor roles.\n\nOn January 14, 2018 he released his first official called single \"Inviting All of You\".<ref>{{cite web |title=Inviting All of You - Single |url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/inviting-all-of-you-single/1334762528 |website=iTunes}}</ref> On August 13, 2018, it was announced that JD McCrary became the youngest artist to sign with [[Disney Music Group]]'s [[Hollywood Records]], as he released the music video to his second single \"My Name\" on August 28.<ref>{{cite web |title=Jd Mccrary, Youngest Solo Artist To Sign With Hollywood Records Releases 'My Name' Video |url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwmusic/article/Jd-Mccrary-Youngest-Solo-Artist-To-Sign-With-Hollywood-Records-Releases-My-Name-Video-20180828 |website=Broadway World}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=THE LION KING'S JD McCrary Signs to Hollywood Records |url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwmusic/article/THE-LION-KINGS-JD-McCrary-Signs-to-Hollywood-Records-20180813 |website=Broadway World |accessdate=27 November 2018}}</ref> On January 24, 2019, he released the first single after signing to the label called \"Keep in Touch.\"<ref>{{cite web |title=JD MCCRARY RELEASES NEW SINGLE \u2018KEEP IN TOUCH\u2019 |url=http://tigerbeat.com/video/jd-mccrary-keep-in-touch/ |website=Tiger Beat}}</ref> He stars in ''[[The Paynes]]'' on the [[Oprah Winfrey Network]].\n\nIn 2019, McCrary co-starred in the [[Universal Pictures|Universal]] comedy film ''[[Little (film)|Little]]'', and provided the voice of young [[Simba]] in the live action remake of the [[Walt Disney Pictures|Disney]] film ''[[The Lion King (2019 film)|The Lion King]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|title=OWN Picks Up \u2018House of Payne\u2019 Spinoff From Tyler Perry|url=http://deadline.com/2017/01/own-the-paynes-house-of-payne-spinoff-tyler-perry-more-the-haves-and-have-nots-if-loving-you-is-wrong-love-thy-neighbor-cnaceled-for-better-or-worse-1201897435/|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=January 30, 2017|accessdate=February 21, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Galuppo |first1=Mia |title='Lion King' Actor JD McCrary Joins Marsai Martin in 'Little' (Exclusive) |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/little-movie-lion-king-actor-jd-mccrary-joins-universal-comedy-1121119 |website=Hollywood Reporter}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Davis|first1=Justin|title=The 10-Year-Old Playing Simba Alongside Donald Glover Has A Cooler Life Than You|url=http://www.complex.com/pop-culture/2017/12/jd-mccrary-lion-king-interview|website=Complex|date=December 8, 2017|accessdate=February 21, 2018}}</ref> McCrary said that \"[[Donald Glover]] [who voices adult Simba] is so talented that [I] actually did have to take it into consideration, because if Simba is going to grow up to be some sort of figure and you know of it, you have to keep that motive.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ftRPVHyELXo&t=19s|title=What To Expect From The Characters In The Upcoming 'The Lion King' Adaptation - Entertainment Weekly|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]/[[YouTube]]|language=en|date=April 25, 2019|access-date=April 29, 2019|url-status=live|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Also that year, McCrary also portrays a young [[Michael Jackson]] in the [[BET]] series ''[[American Soul]]'', which premiered in February. On April 19, McCrary released his debut EP, ''Shine'', which includes production from [[Jermaine Dupri]] and [[Bryan-Michael Cox]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Shine - EP by JD McCrary |url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/shine-ep/1459186620 |website=iTunes |accessdate=22 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Artistry==\nIn an interview with ''[[Vibe (magazine)|Vibe]]'', McCrary cited [[Michael Jackson]] as his biggest influence, as well as [[Stevie Wonder]], [[Bruno Mars]], [[Justin Bieber]], and [[Chris Brown]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Jefferson|first1=J'na|title=Interview: JD McCrary Talks \u2018The Lion King,\u2019 Working With Donald Glover|url=https://www.vibe.com/2017/11/jd-mccrary-interview/|website=Vibe|date=November 28, 2017|accessdate=March 22, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n===Extended plays===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:11em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:18em;\"| EP details\n|- \n! scope=\"row\" | ''Shine''\n|\n* Released: April 19, 2019\n* Label: [[Hollywood Records]]\n* Format: Digital download \n|}\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\"| Year\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Inviting All of You\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2018\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"My Name\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Keep in Touch\"\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2019\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Where Do I Belong\"\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Closer to Christmas\"\n|}\n\n===Guest appearances===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ List of guest appearances, with other performing artists, showing year released and album name\n!Title !! Other artist(s) !! Year !! Album\n|- \n| \"[[Terrified (song)|Terrified]]\" || [[Donald Glover|Childish Gambino]] || 2016 || ''[[\"Awaken, My Love!\"]]''\n|-\n| \"Cautionary Tales\" || [[Jon Bellion]] || rowspan=\"2\"|2018 || ''Glory Sound Prep''\n|-\n| \"This Neverland\" || [[G Tom Mac]] || ''A Lost Boys Story: The Musical (Original Score)''\