ion Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Poland|artist=\u00c1lvaro Soler|title=Mar de Colores|award=Gold|type=album|relyear=2018|certyear=2019|accessdate=13 June 2019}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{\u00c1lvaro Soler}}\n\n[[Category:2018 albums]]\n[[Category:\u00c1lvaro Soler albums]]\n[[Category:Spanish-language albums]]\n\n{{2010s-album-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{use dmy dates|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Mar de Colores\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[\u00c1lvaro Soler]]\n| cover      = Mar de Colores.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{Start date|2018|09|07|df=y}}\n| recorded   =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = <!--Do not add unsourced genres -->\n| length     = 56:28\n| label      = {{hlist|Airforce 1|[[Universal Music]]}}\n| producer   = {{hlist|B-Case|FNSHRS|T.I. Jakke|David J\u00fcrgens|William Larsen|Kalli|George Noriega|[[RedOne]]|Stengaard|Tricot}}\n| prev_title = [[Eterno Agosto]]\n| prev_year  = 2015\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Mar de Colores\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[La Cintura (song)|La Cintura]]\n | single1date = 29 March 2018\n | single2     = [[Loca (\u00c1lvaro Soler song)|Loca]]\n | single2date = 25 January 2019\n | single3     = [[La Libertad (\u00c1lvaro Soler song)|La Libertad]]\n | single3date = 10 May 2019\n}}\n}}\n'''''Mar de Colores''''' ([[English language|English]]: ''Sea of Colors'') is the second studio album by Spanish-German singer-songwriter [[\u00c1lvaro Soler]]. It was released on 7 September 2018 by Airforce1 Records and [[Universal Music]]. \n\nAn expanded version of the deluxe edition of the album, subtitled ''Versi\u00f3n Extendida'', was released on 10 May 2019. It features three new songs, \"[[Loca (\u00c1lvaro Soler song)|Loca]]\", \"[[La Libertad (\u00c1lvaro Soler song)|La Libertad]]\" and \"Taro\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/de/album/mar-de-colores-versi%C3%B3n-extendida/1457720122|title=\u00c1lvaro Soler \u2013 Mar de Colores (Versi\u00f3n Extendida) \u2013 Album|via=iTunes Store|accessdate=15 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| headline        = ''Mar de Colores'' \u2013 {{nobold|Standard edition}}\n| extra_column    = Producers\n| total_length    = 33:50\n\n| title1          = [[La Cintura (song)|La Cintura]]\n| writer1         = {{hlist|Soler|Zuckowski|Erixson|[[RedOne|Nadir Khayat]]|Triebel}}\n| extra1          = {{hlist|Zuckowski|[[RedOne]]|Triebel|T.I. Jakke}}\n| length1         = 3:24\n\n| title2          = Hist\u00e9rico\n| writer2         = {{hlist|Soler|Zuckowski|Giencarlos Rivera|Jonathan Carlo Rivera|Triebel}}\n| extra2          = {{hlist|Pascal Reinhard|Tricot}}\n| length2         = 2:58\n\n| title3          = Te Quiero Lento\n| writer3         = {{hlist|Soler|Zuckowski|Andrew Wells|Triebel}}\n| extra3          = {{hlist|Wells|Tricot}}\n| length3         = 3:13\n\n| title4          = Ella\n| writer4         = {{hlist|Soler|Zuckowski|Cris Chil|Max Bernard|Triebel}}\n| extra4          = Tricot\n| length4         = 3:32\n\n| title5          = Puebla\n| writer5         = {{hlist|Soler|Zuckowski|Triebel|[[William Wiik Larsen]]}}\n| extra5          = {{hlist|Tricot|Larsen}}\n| length5         = 3:10\n\n| title6          = Au Au Au\n| writer6         = {{hlist|Soler|Zuckowski|Bruno Valverde|[[George Noriega]]|Paul Irizarry|Triebel}}\n| extra6          = {{hlist|Noriega|Tricot}}\n| length6         = 2:50\n\n| title7          = Fuego\n| note7           = feat. Nico Santos\n| writer7         = {{hlist|Soler|Santos|Zuckowski|[[Andrew Goldstein (musician)|Andrew Goldstein]]|Triebel|Tom Peyton}}\n| extra7          = {{hlist|Thomas Stengaard|Tricot}}\n| length7         = 2:58\n\n| title8          = Veneno\n| writer8         = {{hlist|Soler|Zuckowski|Triebel}}\n| extra8          = {{hlist|B-Case|Tricot}}\n| length8         = 3:14\n\n| title9          = Bonita\n| writer9         = {{hlist|Sol